<h3>Bluetooth Connection before login</h3>
<div class="postmsg">
<p>Hello :),</p><p>i have a question, I own an Acer Iconia W700 and installed Parrot. Everything works fine. But I want to use my Acer to-go without needing a usb keyboard so I connected the Bluetooth key. See the picture for the keyboard. I connected it and it works really great, changed layout to de_DE. But my problem is that i cannot login. The Bluetooth connection works only after I logged in my account or as root user. I selected the keyboard as trusted for booth users. But it doesn&#039;t work on login. Then i had the idea to just disable the password for login so I don&#039;t need to annoy you, but the checkbox is disabled. So i now need to annoy you and ask you how can I enable the keyboard for the login screen or enable autologin to use my keyboard. I hope you can understand everything because english isn&#039;t my native language.</p><p>Thank you and have a nice day :)</p><p><span class="postimg"><img src="https://s16.postimg.org/6ozey56ox/Acer_W700_in_Case_vorne_rcm992x0.jpg" alt="Acer_W700_in_Case_vorne_rcm992x0.jpg"/></span></p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
